HEADWORD: Sparth
<hw>Sparth</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Icel.
<ets>spar<?/a</ets>.]</ety> <def>An Anglo-Saxon battle-ax, or
halberd.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He hath a <qex>sparth</qex> of twenty pound of weight.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

